1
00:00:36,270 --> 00:00:39,670
The Tale Of Despereaux
浪漫的老鼠

2
00:02:05,670 --> 00:02:07,170
Once upon a time,
很久很久以前

3
00:02:07,370 --> 00:02:09,470
there was a brave little mouse
有一只勇敢的小老鼠

4
00:02:09,570 --> 00:02:13,270
who loved honor and justice and always told the truth.
他自尊自爱 明辨是非 总是据实直言

5
00:02:27,770 --> 00:02:29,570
No, that's not him.
不 这个不是他

6
00:02:31,270 --> 00:02:32,670
That's a rat.
这是只耗子

7
00:02:33,070 --> 00:02:34,170
And anyone who knows anything,
任何有常识的人都知道

8
00:02:34,270 --> 00:02:36,770
knows there's a big difference between a mouse and a rat.
老鼠和耗子是有很大区别的

9
00:02:38,170 --> 00:02:40,970
First of all, rats hate the light.
首先 耗子讨厌阳光

10
00:02:43,670 --> 00:02:46,270
They spend their lives in the darkness.
他们一辈子活在黑暗里

11
00:02:46,570 --> 00:02:47,870
They're also terrified of people,
而且他们害怕人类

12
00:02:47,970 --> 00:02:50,070
which is why they slink and cower all the time.
所以他们总是偷偷摸摸 东躲西藏

13
00:02:51,570 --> 00:02:53,770
And as far as telling the truth is concerned,
而关于"据实直言"

14
00:02:53,870 --> 00:02:56,570
well, that's impossible because, as everyone knows,
这是不可能的 因为谁都知道

15
00:02:58,070 --> 00:02:59,770
a rat can't talk.
耗子不会说话

16
00:02:59,970 --> 00:03:01,470
Tell me that thing again, please.
再跟我说一次 求你了

17
00:03:01,870 --> 00:03:03,070
Come on.
拜托

18
00:03:03,770 --> 00:03:05,070
Just once, I promise.
最后一次 我保证

19
00:03:05,170 --> 00:03:06,270
Tell me one more time,
再对我说一次

20
00:03:06,370 --> 00:03:08,070
and I won't ask you ever again. I swear.
我就不会再问你了 我发誓

21
00:03:09,270 --> 00:03:12,170
Fine. We are headed to Dor,
好吧 我们要去多尔国

22
00:03:12,270 --> 00:03:15,070
one of the most magical places in the whole world.
世界上最神奇的地方之一

23
00:03:15,170 --> 00:03:16,670
No, that's not what you said before.
不 你之前不是这样说的

24
00:03:16,770 --> 00:03:19,370
You know, every place has something special.
每个地方都有独一无二的东西

25
00:03:19,470 --> 00:03:21,870
And, in Dor, it's the soup!
在多尔 最特别的是汤!

26
00:03:22,070 --> 00:03:23,770
Land ho!
陆地!

27
00:03:30,170 --> 00:03:31,570
It's down below, I tell you.
就在下面 我告诉过你

28
00:03:31,570 --> 00:03:32,670
Give it a heave.
使劲拉

29
00:03:37,770 --> 00:03:39,170
I can see it!
我看见它了!

30
00:03:41,670 --> 00:03:45,370
Ooh, I can smell it! I can smell it.
哦 我能闻到它! 我能闻到它

31
00:03:52,770 --> 00:03:55,270
Oh, I can't wait to taste the soup!
喔 我等不及想尝尝这儿的汤!

32
00:03:55,570 --> 00:03:57,070
Just stay close.
别乱跑

33
00:03:57,170 --> 00:03:58,370
We leave again at 6:00.
我们六点要离开

34
00:03:58,470 --> 00:04:01,270
You know, we ought to think about staying here just a little longer.
知道么 我们该考虑在这儿多待一会儿

35
00:04:01,370 --> 00:04:03,370
Don't even think about it.
想都别想

36
00:04:03,670 --> 00:04:04,770
Remember Shanghai?
还记得上海吗?

37
00:04:04,770 --> 00:04:06,370
Yeah, but this place is different.
记得 但这里不同

38
00:04:06,770 --> 00:04:08,770
I mean, this is special.
我是说 这儿很特别

39
00:04:11,270 --> 00:04:14,970
On any given day, just one whiff from one of the soup shops
在这里的每一天 闻一下汤店里飘出的香气

40
00:04:15,070 --> 00:04:17,470
was almost like having a full meal.
就犹如让你饱餐一顿

41
00:04:18,170 --> 00:04:21,170
But on one very special day every year,
但在每年一个特殊的日子里

42
00:04:21,170 --> 00:04:24,170
the kingdom of Dor was magically transformed.
多尔举国上下热闹非凡

43
00:04:26,870 --> 00:04:28,770
In Dor, Christmas was nothing.
在多尔 圣诞节不值一提

44
00:04:28,970 --> 00:04:30,470
Well, they still celebrated it,
虽然他们仍然庆祝圣诞节

45
00:04:30,570 --> 00:04:33,270
but it was nothing compared to Soup Day.
但和汤节相比 那就是小巫见大巫

46
00:04:38,370 --> 00:04:39,370
Watch it, watch it.
小心 小心

47
00:04:39,470 --> 00:04:41,370
Incoming potatoes!
土豆来啦!

48
00:04:41,470 --> 00:04:43,170
Hurry! Hurry! Excuse us.
快啊! 快啊! 请让让

49
00:04:43,270 --> 00:04:46,370
Every Dorian, young and old, would flock toward the castle
每个多尔人 无论老幼 都会聚集在城堡周围

50
00:04:46,470 --> 00:04:49,470
because they knew that, at that very moment,
因为他们知道 此时此刻

51
00:04:49,570 --> 00:04:52,170
deep within the royal kitchens,
皇室厨房的深处

52
00:04:52,270 --> 00:04:54,170
a masterpiece was being created.
一件杰作即将诞生

53
00:04:54,270 --> 00:04:55,970
Potatoes coming up!
土豆来啦!

54
00:05:03,370 --> 00:05:04,470
Let's go!
开工啦!

55
00:05:04,570 --> 00:05:05,570
Don't forget the parsley!
别忘记欧芹!

56
00:05:05,870 --> 00:05:07,370
Make sure it's clean!
把欧芹洗干净!

57
00:05:18,370 --> 00:05:20,570
Everyone knew Chef Andre was a genius,
全国上下都知道厨师Andre是个天才

58
00:05:20,670 --> 00:05:24,970
but they got reminded of it on the first Sunday of every spring.
但在每年春天的第一个星期日 大家还是会被再次提醒

59
00:05:26,870 --> 00:05:29,170
At exactly 12:00 noon,
中午十二点整

60
00:05:29,270 --> 00:05:32,670
he would unveil that year's royal creation.
他会献上当年皇室厨房的新作

61
00:05:45,670 --> 00:05:47,970
More onions!
加洋葱!

62
00:05:48,070 --> 00:05:49,070
More onions!
加洋葱!

63
00:05:49,170 --> 00:05:50,270
More onions!
加洋葱!

64
00:05:49,183 --> 00:05:50,241
加洋葱!

65
00:05:51,870 --> 00:05:53,870
They would jam the town square,
百姓们聚集在广场上翘首以盼

66
00:05:53,870 --> 00:05:56,170
and, as the aroma began to build,
随着香气越来越浓

67
00:05:56,270 --> 00:05:58,370
so did their anticipation.
他们的期待也越来越高

68
00:06:03,070 --> 00:06:04,070
Sorry.
对不起

69
00:06:16,370 --> 00:06:17,470
Thank you.
谢谢

70
00:06:18,770 --> 00:06:23,570
It's my pleasure to announce this year's royal creations
我很荣幸为大家宣布 今年皇室厨房的新作品

71
00:06:23,870 --> 00:06:26,170
from the kitchens of Chef Andre.
Andre厨房最新研制的汤

72
00:06:26,670 --> 00:06:27,970
Oh, no, no, no, no, no!
不 不 不 不 不 不!

73
00:06:28,070 --> 00:06:29,470
Something is wrong.
哪里不对劲

74
00:06:29,570 --> 00:06:31,170
I need more time!
我需要时间!

75
00:06:31,370 --> 00:06:32,570
But we're late already!
可我们已经晚点了!

76
00:06:32,670 --> 00:06:34,270
This is not right!
这汤不对劲!

77
00:06:36,470 --> 00:06:37,870
Everyone out!
所有人都出去!

78
00:06:38,370 --> 00:06:39,370
Out!
出去!

79
00:06:42,870 --> 00:06:46,570
Now, it's hard to be a genius all by yourself.
要当一个天才 孤军奋战是很难的

80
00:06:47,070 --> 00:06:50,870
In fact, sometimes, it takes a little help.
事实上 有时 天才也需要帮手

81
00:07:14,270 --> 00:07:15,670
You changed something.
汤被你动了手脚

82
00:07:15,970 --> 00:07:18,070
You're crazy. I did not touch it.
你疯了 我什么都没碰

83
00:07:18,170 --> 00:07:19,270
- I can smell it. - Hmm?
- 我闻得出来 - 嗯?

84
00:07:19,370 --> 00:07:20,470
- What's this? - What?
- 这是什么? - 什么?

85
00:07:20,470 --> 00:07:22,170
- This! - Ow! Garlic.
- 这个! - 嗷! 是大蒜

86
00:07:22,570 --> 00:07:23,770
- Garlic. - Yeah, a little garlic.
- 大蒜 - 是的 一颗小蒜头

87
00:07:24,370 --> 00:07:25,870
- It was already there. - No.
- 本来就要加蒜的 - 不是

88
00:07:25,970 --> 00:07:26,970
- Yes. - No.
- 是的 - 不是

89
00:07:27,070 --> 00:07:28,170
- Yes. - Not this much!
- 是的 - 不是加那么多!

90
00:07:29,370 --> 00:07:30,470
You ruined my soup!
你毁了我的汤!

91
00:07:30,570 --> 00:07:31,970
I save your soup!
我救了你的汤!

92
00:07:32,070 --> 00:07:37,070
Those people wait all year, and you want to give them this dishwater.
全国上下盼了一整年 你难道就给他们喝洗碗水

93
00:07:37,870 --> 00:07:39,170
Dishwater?
洗碗水

94
00:07:39,270 --> 00:07:40,470
Dishwater.
洗碗水

95
00:07:40,570 --> 00:07:41,670
Dishwater?
洗碗水?

96
00:07:41,770 --> 00:07:42,870
Ow! Cut it out!
嗷! 住手!

97
00:07:47,070 --> 00:07:48,770
And this year's soup is
今年的汤是...

98
00:07:50,870 --> 00:07:52,770
a spring tureen
一碗甘泉

99
00:07:52,873 --> 00:07:54,602
配上各种烘烤过的蔬菜... with a mlange of roasted vegetables...

100
00:07:55,770 --> 00:07:57,570
...fresh herbs... - Mmm!
新鲜的香草...

101
00:07:57,670 --> 00:07:59,270
...and wild mushrooms.
还有野生蘑菇

102
00:08:01,170 --> 00:08:02,470
Roscuro?
Roscuro?

103
00:08:06,570 --> 00:08:08,070
Roscuro?
Roscuro?

104
00:08:08,670 --> 00:08:10,470
Oh. Evening.
哦 你好啊

105
00:08:14,470 --> 00:08:18,870
I don't have to stand here and listen to a big talking garbage can!
我没必要站在这儿 听一个垃圾桶说话!

106
00:08:19,070 --> 00:08:22,670
Ha! And I don't have to stand here and listen to a coward!
哈! 我更没必要站在这儿 听一个胆小鬼说话!

107
00:08:22,970 --> 00:08:24,570
- Coward? - Yes, a coward!
- 胆小鬼? - 是的 胆小鬼!

108
00:08:24,670 --> 00:08:26,470
- You call me coward? - Yes!
- 你说我胆小? - 没错!

109
00:08:30,570 --> 00:08:32,070
Oh, no!
喔 不!

110
00:08:49,570 --> 00:08:51,070
Oh, no, no, no, no, no.
喔 不 不 不 不 不

111
00:08:51,170 --> 00:08:52,670
That did it.
这回完蛋了

112
00:08:57,070 --> 00:08:58,870
- Hmm? - Mmm.
- 嗯? - 嗯

113
00:09:02,570 --> 00:09:04,870
- Bellissima! - It's fantastique!
- 极品! - 太棒了!

114
00:09:04,870 --> 00:09:07,870
Roscuro! Roscuro, where are you?
Roscuro! Roscuro 你在哪儿?

115
00:09:55,570 --> 00:09:56,670
Voil?
请用

116
00:09:56,970 --> 00:10:00,070
This is amazing!
令人叹为观止!

117
00:10:00,270 --> 00:10:01,970
Wait till Your Highness tastes it.
请殿下您品尝

118
00:10:04,270 --> 00:10:05,270
Hmm?
呃?

119
00:10:17,170 --> 00:10:18,470
This is...
这汤真是...

120
00:10:19,770 --> 00:10:21,770
...absolutely...
简直是...

121
00:10:22,970 --> 00:10:26,770
Oh, it moved! My soup moved!
哦 它动了! 我的汤动了!

122
00:10:26,970 --> 00:10:29,170
No, it isn't... It did not move.
不 它没有... 它没动

123
00:10:29,870 --> 00:10:30,970
Oh, Your Highness.
哦 殿下

124
00:10:31,170 --> 00:10:32,170
- Ahhh! - Darling?
- 啊! - 亲爱的?

125
00:10:32,270 --> 00:10:35,270
Oh! A rat! There's a rat in my soup!
哦! 耗子! 我汤里有一只耗子!

126
00:10:35,370 --> 00:10:36,970
Madam, I know that this is unfortunate.
夫人 我知道这令人不快

127
00:10:37,070 --> 00:10:39,270
And I know that while on first glance, I might...
我知道 乍看之下 我可能...

128
00:10:39,370 --> 00:10:41,470
- A rat! In my soup! - No. Please. Shh, shh, shh.
- 一只耗子! 在我的汤里! - 不 求你 嘘 嘘 嘘

129
00:10:41,570 --> 00:10:43,670
- And I ate it! - Your Highness, hold on...
- 我喝了! - 陛下 等等...

130
00:10:44,870 --> 00:10:46,670
- Uh-oh. - She's right! It's a rat!
- 啊哦 - 她没说错! 是只耗子!

131
00:10:47,870 --> 00:10:49,970
- Please... - Ahhh! It's a rat!
- 拜托... - 啊! 是只耗子!

132
00:10:50,770 --> 00:10:53,870
Get me that rat!
给我 抓住 那只 耗子!

133
00:10:54,170 --> 00:10:55,870
Now, I really believe you're jumping to conclusions.
我真觉得您的决定太草率了

134
00:10:56,370 --> 00:10:57,870
And I'm sure that the rats you met last time
我肯定 你遇见的上一只耗子

135
00:10:57,970 --> 00:11:00,170
might have caused you to create a stereotype,
对你造成了很大困扰 使你对我有偏见

136
00:11:00,270 --> 00:11:01,870
but... But I... But...
但是... 但是 我... 但是...

137
00:11:01,970 --> 00:11:04,170
It's just... I'm just... I'm not really from around here.
只是... 我只是...我不是这个国家的

138
00:11:04,270 --> 00:11:05,970
I'm... I'm from... Oh...
我... 我来自... 哦...

139
00:11:07,270 --> 00:11:08,770
That's very aggressive.
太暴力了

140
00:11:09,270 --> 00:11:10,370
Get him!
抓住他!

141
00:11:10,470 --> 00:11:11,570
Kitchen...
厨房...

142
00:11:11,670 --> 00:11:12,870
He's going into the kitchen!
他跑到厨房去了!

143
00:11:21,170 --> 00:11:22,270
Over there!
在那儿!

144
00:11:23,470 --> 00:11:25,070
Stop that rat!
抓住那只耗子!

145
00:11:27,870 --> 00:11:28,970
I got him!
我抓住它了!

146
00:11:37,070 --> 00:11:39,670
He's going near the soup!
它朝汤附近去了!

147
00:11:43,070 --> 00:11:44,070
There he is!
他在这儿!

148
00:11:44,270 --> 00:11:46,170
lf... If I could just tell...
能不能...能不能让我说两句...

149
00:11:46,670 --> 00:11:49,570
On the kettle! That's him, right there!
在茶壶上! 它在那儿 就在那儿!

150
00:11:53,970 --> 00:11:54,970
Look, up there!
瞧 在上面!

151
00:12:05,270 --> 00:12:07,070
Sweetie? Darling?
亲爱的? 甜心?

152
00:12:08,570 --> 00:12:10,070
She's... She's...
她... 她...

153
00:12:11,570 --> 00:12:14,170
She's...
她...

154
00:12:14,870 --> 00:12:17,570
Blimey, she's dead. Get him!
老天啊 她死了 抓住它!

155
00:12:17,670 --> 00:12:19,370
Don't let him escape!
别让他逃了!

156
00:12:19,470 --> 00:12:21,770
We'll get you, you rowdy rat!
我们要抓住你这只可恶的耗子!

157
00:12:28,470 --> 00:12:29,570
No, no, no!
不 不 不!

158
00:12:29,570 --> 00:12:31,370
No, not there!
不 不能掉在那里!

159
00:13:32,970 --> 00:13:35,170
You don't need to be afraid.
你不必害怕

160
00:13:36,370 --> 00:13:39,270
I know it's dark, but you'll get used to it.
我知道这儿很黑 但你会习惯的

161
00:13:39,970 --> 00:13:41,770
Who... Who are you?
你... 你是谁?

162
00:13:42,570 --> 00:13:44,870
Just a rat, like you.
我只是耗子 和你一样

163
00:13:46,570 --> 00:13:47,970
Come with me.
跟我来

164
00:14:00,470 --> 00:14:04,270
When something hurts this much, there must be a reason.
伤痛如此深重 肯定有其缘由

165
00:14:05,170 --> 00:14:07,470
There must be someone to blame.
肯定有罪魁祸首

166
00:14:13,970 --> 00:14:17,070
"From this moment on, soup,
从此刻起 汤...

167
00:14:17,170 --> 00:14:22,670
"the making of soup, the selling of soup, or the eating of soup,
制作汤 卖汤 或者喝汤...

168
00:14:22,970 --> 00:14:26,170
"is hereby outlawed in the kingdom of Dor!
在多尔国境内将被法律禁止!

169
00:14:34,170 --> 00:14:37,570
"Rats are to be considered illegal as well
耗子也将不容于法律

170
00:14:37,670 --> 00:14:42,270
"and are hereby deemed unlawful creatures in the kingdom of Dor!
在此宣布耗子是多尔国的非法动物!

171
00:14:42,370 --> 00:14:43,670
"From this moment on,
从此刻起

172
00:14:43,770 --> 00:14:48,970
"anyone harboring, sheltering or possessing a rat in any way,
以任何方式藏匿 收容或圈养耗子的人

173
00:14:49,070 --> 00:14:51,670
"shall face the full wrath of the law!"
都将受到法律的严惩!

174
00:14:52,970 --> 00:14:54,770
So think about this.
设想一下

175
00:14:54,870 --> 00:14:59,870
What happens when you make something illegal that is just a natural part of the world?
将大自然的一部分定为非法 会有什么结果呢?

176
00:15:01,470 --> 00:15:03,570
You may as well make flies illegal.
你也可以说苍蝇是非法的

177
00:15:03,670 --> 00:15:05,870
Or sweat. Or Monday morning.
或者汗 或者星期一早晨

178
00:15:06,770 --> 00:15:10,270
But that's what the King did out of a terrible sadness.
但国王偏偏就这样做了 因为沉重的悲伤

179
00:15:14,470 --> 00:15:17,070
Sunlight left and the world went gray.
红日西斜 夜幕降临

180
00:15:18,370 --> 00:15:22,370
Colors faded into each other and dark clouds filled the sky.
世界渐渐褪色 乌云遮蔽天空

181
00:15:24,470 --> 00:15:28,470
And for a long time, it wouldn't rain.
很长一段时间 滴雨未落

182
00:15:32,270 --> 00:15:38,270
The clouds just stayed and stayed and stayed.
乌云盘踞在头顶 久久不能散去

183
00:15:48,570 --> 00:15:50,370
I wish it would rain.
真希望能下一场雨

184
00:15:51,170 --> 00:15:52,670
You and the whole world, madam.
你和大家一样 殿下

185
00:15:54,770 --> 00:15:55,870
Oh, sorry, milady!
哦 对不起 殿下!

186
00:15:56,570 --> 00:15:59,070
Well, at least I can still feel that.
没关系 至少我还能感觉到疼痛

187
00:16:02,170 --> 00:16:06,170
Louise, do you think there's a bit of light
Louise 你觉得世上的某处...

188
00:16:06,870 --> 00:16:07,970
somewhere in the world?
是否还有一丝光明?

189
00:16:08,470 --> 00:16:09,570
Don't know, ma'am.
我不知道 殿下

190
00:16:09,670 --> 00:16:11,270
I think there is.
我想一定有

191
00:16:12,270 --> 00:16:14,870
You just need to know where to find it.
只是你得知道 去哪儿找这丝光明

192
00:16:27,070 --> 00:16:29,470
Okay, remember when we told you how,
好了 还记得刚才我说的...

193
00:16:29,570 --> 00:16:32,370
once upon a time, there was this brave little mouse?
很久很久以前 有一只勇敢的小老鼠?

194
00:16:32,470 --> 00:16:36,070
Well, if you know anything about fairytales,
如果你了解童话故事

195
00:16:36,170 --> 00:16:40,170
you know that a hero doesn't appear
你就该知道 英雄不轻易出现

196
00:16:40,470 --> 00:16:42,770
until the world really needs one.
除非世界没他不行

197
00:16:56,670 --> 00:16:57,770
Oh, look out!
喔 小心!

198
00:16:57,870 --> 00:17:01,070
Alms for the blind! Alms for the blind!
谁来施舍我这个可怜的瞎子!

199
00:17:20,487 --> 00:17:24,317
老鼠的世界

200
00:17:39,270 --> 00:17:40,570
Excuse me. Excuse me.
对不起 对不起

201
00:17:41,170 --> 00:17:42,470
Excuse me.
对不起

202
00:17:42,970 --> 00:17:44,370
Excuse me.
对不起

203
00:17:45,070 --> 00:17:46,470
- Whoa! - I'm sorry. Sorry.
- 哇喔! - 对不起 对不起

204
00:17:46,570 --> 00:17:47,770
- Tilling? - Oh!
- Tilling? - 哦!

205
00:17:48,170 --> 00:17:49,870
Mr. Mayor, hello!
镇长先生 你好啊!

206
00:17:49,970 --> 00:17:51,170
Where are you going?
你这是要去哪儿?

207
00:17:51,170 --> 00:17:55,070
Oh, well, my baby is having a...
哦 是这样的 我的孩子要生...

208
00:17:55,170 --> 00:17:58,270
No, my wife is having a...
不 我妻子要生...

209
00:17:58,370 --> 00:18:00,470
Oh, right. Congratulations.
哦 好吧 恭喜你了

210
00:18:00,770 --> 00:18:02,070
Thank you. Thank you, sir.
谢谢 谢谢你 先生

211
00:18:02,670 --> 00:18:04,970
I'm sorry, I... I really... Goodbye.
对不起 我...我真的...再见

212
00:18:14,070 --> 00:18:15,670
His eyes are open.
他的眼睛睁得老大了

213
00:18:15,770 --> 00:18:17,170
Don't worry about it.
别担心

214
00:18:17,270 --> 00:18:18,870
Sometimes they are.
有时候 是会这样

215
00:18:19,070 --> 00:18:20,570
But he isn't cowering.
可是他一点都不害怕

216
00:18:20,670 --> 00:18:22,470
He's looking right at us.
他正盯着我们看

217
00:18:22,570 --> 00:18:24,970
Don't worry. He'll learn to cower.
别担心 他会学会害怕的

218
00:18:25,470 --> 00:18:27,170
They all do in time.
到一定时候 他们都会学会的

219
00:18:28,070 --> 00:18:29,570
But he isn't!
可他没有!

220
00:18:36,470 --> 00:18:40,770
Wow! He's so puny! And look at those ears!
哇喔! 他真好玩儿! 瞧那对耳朵!

221
00:18:41,770 --> 00:18:43,170
And, from the very beginning,
打从一开始

222
00:18:43,270 --> 00:18:45,470
Despereaux Tilling heard more,
Despereaux Tilling就比他的同类

223
00:18:45,570 --> 00:18:49,370
saw more and even smelled more than any of the other mice.
听得更多 看得更多 闻得更多

224
00:18:55,170 --> 00:18:57,170
Despereaux, don't do it.
Despereaux 别这么做

225
00:19:08,370 --> 00:19:09,570
Don't look. Don't look!
别看 别看!

226
00:19:09,670 --> 00:19:10,770
I won't, I won't.
我不看 我不看

227
00:19:20,570 --> 00:19:23,470
Despereaux Tilling had no idea he was small.
Despereaux Tilling并不觉得自己很小

228
00:19:24,570 --> 00:19:27,070
He wasn't just small in human terms.
其实他的个子 不仅比起人类很小

229
00:19:27,270 --> 00:19:29,770
He was small even for a mouse.
连比起老鼠都算小

230
00:19:30,470 --> 00:19:33,570
But, to tell you the truth, he didn't even notice.
但实话告诉你吧 他自己一点没感觉

231
00:19:33,870 --> 00:19:38,170
In fact, in his own mind, Despereaux was a giant.
事实上 在他看来 Despereaux是个巨人

232
00:19:47,970 --> 00:19:49,770
We're worried about him.
我们很担心他

233
00:19:49,870 --> 00:19:51,970
He doesn't scurry. He doesn't cower.
他不逃跑 也不害怕

234
00:19:51,970 --> 00:19:54,270
At first, we thought he would grow out of it, but...
起先 我们以为他能慢慢学会 可是...

235
00:19:54,370 --> 00:19:56,270
Well, he scurries sometimes.
他有时跑得挺快

236
00:19:56,370 --> 00:19:57,670
But not when he's scared!
但那不是出于害怕!

237
00:19:57,770 --> 00:19:58,770
He just does it for fun.
他只是在闹着玩

238
00:19:58,970 --> 00:20:00,470
And he never cowers.
他从不害怕

239
00:20:00,570 --> 00:20:01,670
We've showed him how, but he...
我们试图教他 可他...

240
00:20:01,770 --> 00:20:04,270
Well, some kids are slower than others.
有些孩子是学得比较慢

241
00:20:04,370 --> 00:20:06,470
He'll cower in time. We'll work on it.
他会学会害怕 我们会帮他

242
00:20:06,570 --> 00:20:09,070
- Yes, but... - It'll be fine, I promise.
- 好吧 不过... - 会好起来的 我保证

243
00:20:09,770 --> 00:20:11,670
All right, settle down.
好了 大家安静

244
00:20:12,270 --> 00:20:13,770
Ready, class?
准备好了么?

245
00:20:19,670 --> 00:20:20,770
Good.
很好

246
00:20:23,170 --> 00:20:24,670
Mmm! Ah!
嗯嗯

247
00:20:25,670 --> 00:20:27,270
Good. Excellent.
很好 非常好

248
00:20:37,870 --> 00:20:40,170
- Despereaux! - Yes?
- Despereaux! - 什么事?

249
00:20:40,270 --> 00:20:41,370
You didn't cower.
你没害怕

250
00:20:41,970 --> 00:20:42,970
Looks like a sword.
看起来像一把宝剑

251
00:20:43,070 --> 00:20:45,570
It's a carving knife.
这是一把餐刀

252
00:20:46,670 --> 00:20:48,870
It's beautiful!
它太美了!

253
00:20:48,970 --> 00:20:50,470
It's dangerous.
它很危险

254
00:20:50,770 --> 00:20:52,770
Do you have anymore?
你还有吗?

255
00:20:56,670 --> 00:20:58,670
Despereaux, what are you doing?
Despereaux 你在干嘛?

256
00:20:58,770 --> 00:21:00,270
We're not even supposed to be here.
我们不该到这儿来

257
00:21:00,370 --> 00:21:01,870
That's the dungeon.
那是地牢

258
00:21:02,070 --> 00:21:03,470
They have rats down there.
下面都是耗子

259
00:21:03,570 --> 00:21:04,970
And they'll eat you.
他们会吃掉你的

260
00:21:05,070 --> 00:21:06,970
And pull your arms off!
还会把你的胳臂撕下来!

261
00:21:10,370 --> 00:21:12,070
How far down is it?
下面有多深?

262
00:21:13,170 --> 00:21:15,570
I don't know. No one's ever come back.
我不知道 没人从那儿回来过

263
00:21:15,570 --> 00:21:16,870
How come?
怎么会?

264
00:21:16,970 --> 00:21:18,370
'Cause... 'Cause...
因为...因为...

265
00:21:18,570 --> 00:21:20,270
'Cause that's where you go when you get...
因为来这里人的都是...

266
00:21:20,370 --> 00:21:21,770
When you get...
都是...

267
00:21:21,870 --> 00:21:23,070
Banished.
被驱逐的

268
00:21:24,070 --> 00:21:25,370
What do you get banished for?
他们为什么会被驱逐?

269
00:21:25,670 --> 00:21:26,970
Oh, you know.
哦 你知道的

270
00:21:27,070 --> 00:21:28,370
- Rules and... - Breaking.
- 法律... - 破坏了法律

271
00:21:28,470 --> 00:21:29,670
- We can't even... - Talk about it...
- 我们甚至不能... - 谈起...

272
00:21:29,770 --> 00:21:30,870
- Because... - That's one of the...
- 因为... - 这也是...

273
00:21:31,570 --> 00:21:32,570
Rules!
法律!

274
00:21:35,370 --> 00:21:36,770
Despereaux!
Despereaux!

275
00:21:38,370 --> 00:21:40,770
I just want to have a quick look.
我只想稍微看两眼

276
00:21:41,070 --> 00:21:42,870
We got to get out of here!
我们得离开这里!

277
00:21:44,970 --> 00:21:46,170
Oh, gosh. - Oh, no.
- 哦 老天 - 哦 不

278
00:21:46,270 --> 00:21:47,370
Oh, jeez.
哦 上帝

279
00:22:03,370 --> 00:22:05,670
Despereaux! You can't feed them.
Despereaux! 你不能喂他们

280
00:22:09,270 --> 00:22:10,770
Hello?
你好?

281
00:22:16,770 --> 00:22:19,570
Here you go, whoever you are.
去吧 无论那是哪里

282
00:22:29,070 --> 00:22:30,270
Nice.
太好了

283
00:22:43,807 --> 00:22:49,727
耗子的世界

284
00:23:04,170 --> 00:23:05,470
You are crazy!
你疯了

285
00:23:05,570 --> 00:23:06,970
What I say? I said nothing!
我说什么了? 我什么都没说!

286
00:23:07,070 --> 00:23:08,470
Well, you heard exactly what I said.
那你听清楚我说的了

287
00:23:08,570 --> 00:23:10,170
- I say you crazy. - No, no, no, no!
- 我看你是疯了 - 不 不 不 不

288
00:23:26,470 --> 00:23:27,770
Hurry!
快!

289
00:23:41,370 --> 00:23:43,270
Ha! They look hungry, sir.
哈! 他们看起来饿坏了 先生

290
00:23:47,370 --> 00:23:48,770
Dinnertime.
晚餐时间

291
00:24:05,870 --> 00:24:07,470
You're not eating.
你没在吃嘛

292
00:24:07,570 --> 00:24:09,970
Uh, I was.
呃...我吃过了

293
00:24:10,070 --> 00:24:12,370
No, you weren't.
不 你没有

294
00:24:12,470 --> 00:24:15,870
Well, I'm just watching, sir.
我只是来看看 先生

295
00:24:16,370 --> 00:24:19,970
Well, that's not very grateful of you
你好像不太懂得感恩啊

296
00:24:20,070 --> 00:24:23,170
after I've taken you under my wing.
在我把你纳入我羽翼下之后

297
00:24:23,570 --> 00:24:27,870
Well, I'm grateful, really. I am.
我很感激 真的

298
00:24:28,170 --> 00:24:30,070
You miss something, don't you?
你还在怀念什么 是不是?

299
00:24:30,170 --> 00:24:32,070
Uh, no, I don't.
呃 不 我没有

300
00:24:32,170 --> 00:24:34,570
There's nothing up there, Roscuro.
那上面什么都没有 Roscuro

301
00:24:35,170 --> 00:24:36,570
Nothing at all.
什么都没有

302
00:24:36,570 --> 00:24:39,070
Oh, no, I know that! Absolutely.
哦 我明白! 完全明白

303
00:24:39,370 --> 00:24:41,970
Uh, nothing!
呃 呃 什么都没有

304
00:24:42,670 --> 00:24:44,670
Nothing. Nothing at all.
没有 什么都没有

305
00:24:44,870 --> 00:24:46,370
He's a tough one.
他可真顽固

306
00:24:46,470 --> 00:24:49,170
You're not gonna turn him. Nah, you're not.
你改变不了他 改变不了

307
00:24:49,270 --> 00:24:53,770
Oh, I don't know. A rat is a rat.
哦 我不知道 但是耗子就是耗子

308
00:24:54,270 --> 00:24:57,470
It doesn't really matter where you come from.
从那儿来并不重要

309
00:25:27,370 --> 00:25:28,670
I'm sorry.
我很抱歉

310
00:25:40,770 --> 00:25:42,270
He is so weird.
他可真怪

311
00:25:42,370 --> 00:25:43,470
No kidding.
可不是么

312
00:25:44,270 --> 00:25:46,170
That is so beautiful.
真美啊

313
00:25:46,270 --> 00:25:47,670
I wonder what's out there.
真想看看外面什么样

314
00:26:06,470 --> 00:26:08,770
Doesn't scurry.
二月一号 不逃跑

315
00:26:08,870 --> 00:26:10,770
Didn't cower.
二月三号 不害怕

316
00:26:10,870 --> 00:26:12,670
"Didn't cower. Didn't cower.
不害怕 不害怕...

317
00:26:12,770 --> 00:26:14,270
"Wouldn't scurry."
不逃跑

318
00:26:14,370 --> 00:26:17,870
Oh, here's one: "Drew pictures of cats on his notebook."
还有一条 他在笔记本上画了只猫

319
00:26:17,870 --> 00:26:19,970
- No! Cats? - Oh! I can't imagine!
- 不! 猫? - 哦! 不可想象!

320
00:26:20,270 --> 00:26:23,470
I'm afraid so. Named it Fluffy.
但事实如此 还给它取名"毛毛"

321
00:26:24,070 --> 00:26:27,770
- Oh, I had no idea! - Oh! That's terrible.
- 噢 我真不知道这事 - 这太可怕了

322
00:26:29,970 --> 00:26:31,770
- Despereaux. - Yes, sir?
- Despereaux - 是的 先生?

323
00:26:32,070 --> 00:26:33,370
Come in, please.
进来吧

324
00:26:37,370 --> 00:26:39,370
Despereaux, why do you think you're in school?
Despereaux 你觉得你为什么来上学?

325
00:26:40,770 --> 00:26:41,870
To learn?
来学习?

326
00:26:41,970 --> 00:26:43,070
- To learn, yes. - Yes.
- 学习 是的 - 是的

327
00:26:43,170 --> 00:26:44,170
To learn what?
学什么?

328
00:26:45,370 --> 00:26:50,170
To learn how to be a mouse, sir.
学怎么做一只老鼠 先生

329
00:26:50,670 --> 00:26:52,170
That is correct.
说的对

330
00:26:52,270 --> 00:26:54,670
And you can't be a mouse if you don't learn to be afraid.
但如果你不懂害怕 就做不了老鼠

331
00:26:55,470 --> 00:26:57,170
Oh, Despereaux, this...
哦 Despereaux...

332
00:26:57,270 --> 00:27:00,270
There's so many wonderful things in life to be afraid of
生活中有很多美好的事物 值得你去害怕

333
00:27:00,270 --> 00:27:02,170
if you'd just learn how scary they are.
只要你用心去了解它们有多可怕

334
00:27:02,370 --> 00:27:04,570
Yes. Yes, sir.
是的 是的 先生

335
00:27:08,470 --> 00:27:09,670
How about his brother?
他哥哥情况如何?

336
00:27:09,770 --> 00:27:11,070
His brother? What about him?
他哥哥? 什么情况?

337
00:27:11,270 --> 00:27:14,170
Yes, is he, you know, timid?
是的 我意思是他...胆小吗?

338
00:27:14,770 --> 00:27:16,870
Oh! Oh, yes!
哦! 哦 是的!

339
00:27:17,070 --> 00:27:18,770
- Yes, very timid. - Yes. So timid!
- 是的 非常胆小 - 是 特别胆小

340
00:27:18,770 --> 00:27:20,570
As timid as the day is long.
整天都提心吊胆的

341
00:27:20,670 --> 00:27:21,970
Good. Good.
好 好

342
00:27:22,170 --> 00:27:24,870
Sometimes they just need to see the older ones do it.
有时候榜样的作用很重要

343
00:27:24,970 --> 00:27:26,470
No one starts out afraid.
没有老鼠生来就害怕的

344
00:27:26,870 --> 00:27:28,670
- Understood. - Of course.
- 了解了 - 当然

345
00:27:29,470 --> 00:27:30,970
- You coddle that boy, that's the problem. - No.
- 都是你惯的 - 才不是

346
00:27:31,070 --> 00:27:32,070
- Yes, you do. - No, no.
- 是 都是因为你 - 不 没有

347
00:27:32,170 --> 00:27:34,170
- Yes, you do. You've been doing it for years. - He was always...
- 就是你 老这么惯着他 - 他总是...

348
00:27:34,270 --> 00:27:35,370
He's little. I've had to help him.
他还小 我当然得帮他

349
00:27:35,470 --> 00:27:38,070
He's not going to be afraid unless you allow him to be afraid.
你给要是不他机会 他是不会害怕的

350
00:27:38,170 --> 00:27:39,470
Well, Furlough will teach him.
Furlough会教他的

351
00:27:45,870 --> 00:27:46,870
Do what he does.
哥哥做什么你就跟着做

352
00:27:46,970 --> 00:27:48,170
And don't do anything he doesn't.
他没做的千万不要做

353
00:27:48,270 --> 00:27:49,670
And if he's afraid of something...
他要是害怕什么

354
00:27:49,670 --> 00:27:51,370
Then you need to be afraid of it, too.
你也得学着害怕

355
00:28:32,870 --> 00:28:35,070
Come on, Furlough, hurry up!
快 Furlough 快点!

356
00:28:51,570 --> 00:28:54,370
All right, now, you start nibbling right along that edge there.
好了 你从那边上开始慢慢啃

357
00:28:55,270 --> 00:28:58,570
The glue is all right, but it's the pages that taste the best.
胶水就不错 但纸的味道是最好的

358
00:28:59,270 --> 00:29:03,270
Hmm. "Once upon a time." That's great, isn't it?
"很久很久以前" 说的真棒 是不?

359
00:29:03,670 --> 00:29:05,170
"Upon a time."
"很久以前"

360
00:29:05,270 --> 00:29:07,270
And they don't even tell you what time that is yet.
他们都不告诉你到底有多久

361
00:29:07,270 --> 00:29:09,170
It's like you have to find that out.
好像你必须自己去发现

362
00:29:09,270 --> 00:29:12,270
You're not supposed to read it, Despereaux. You're supposed to eat it.
不是让你来读书的 是让你来吃的

363
00:29:13,570 --> 00:29:15,870
Good. I'll come back in an hour.
好了 我一个小时后回来

364
00:29:17,070 --> 00:29:21,470
And no reading! It's a rule.
别读书! 要守规矩

365
00:29:35,170 --> 00:29:38,870
Once upon a time, there lived a fair princess,
"很久很久以前 有一位美丽的公主...

366
00:29:39,870 --> 00:29:42,270
fairer than any in any other land.
她比任何地方的公主都要美丽"

367
00:29:43,570 --> 00:29:45,270
Hmm. Fair.
美丽

368
00:29:46,070 --> 00:29:51,070
And, as the story goes, she was locked up in a faraway castle,
"后来 她被囚禁在了一座遥远的城堡里

369
00:29:51,170 --> 00:29:54,670
where she could see the world but could never touch it.
在那里她可以看到这个世界 却无法触及

370
00:29:57,470 --> 00:29:59,470
She longed for a prince.
她渴望能有位王子...

371
00:30:00,270 --> 00:30:03,370
A brave knight who would deliver her from all of this.
一位勇敢的骑士 来把她从这一切中拯救出去

372
00:30:03,470 --> 00:30:07,370
Someone with courage and honor and decency.
一个勇敢 尊贵 正派的人

373
00:30:13,370 --> 00:30:15,570
But in a cruel and frightened world,
但在这个残酷 危险的世界里

374
00:30:15,670 --> 00:30:17,670
men like this were scarce indeed.
这样的人实在太少了

375
00:30:59,570 --> 00:31:01,770
They lived in a special world
他们生活在一个特别的世界

376
00:31:02,370 --> 00:31:05,770
built on courage and chivalry and honor.
那里崇尚勇气 骑士精神 和荣耀

377
00:31:06,070 --> 00:31:08,170
They pledged their lives to each other.
他们以生命互相盟誓:

378
00:31:08,670 --> 00:31:11,970
To fight for truth, to defend the weak,
捍卫真理 扶助弱小...

379
00:31:12,070 --> 00:31:15,770
to seek justice, and to always...
追寻正义 并永远..."

380
00:31:20,470 --> 00:31:21,870
How was the library?
图书馆怎么样?

381
00:31:21,970 --> 00:31:22,970
Fine.
很好

382
00:31:23,570 --> 00:31:25,270
Spoil your appetite?
把你的胃口养刁了?

383
00:31:25,670 --> 00:31:27,870
No. Helped it, actually.
不 事实上 让胃口变好了

384
00:31:28,470 --> 00:31:30,170
Made me hungrier.
让我更饿了

385
00:31:31,670 --> 00:31:32,970
Good lad.
好孩子

386
00:31:36,070 --> 00:31:37,470
Ha-hah!
阿哈

387
00:31:39,870 --> 00:31:43,370
Did you see they're putting up a new front on the crumb shop?
看到没? 面包屑店换了个新门面

388
00:31:43,470 --> 00:31:46,070
Oh! But I loved the old front. - Quite modern. Yes.
哦! 可我还是喜欢原来的

389
00:31:52,970 --> 00:31:55,170
Did a book ever speak to you?
有没有一本书 曾经跟你说过话?

390
00:31:55,470 --> 00:31:57,970
Almost like it was written for you?
几乎就像是专门为你而写

391
00:31:58,670 --> 00:32:00,570
Despereaux loved it all.
Despereaux爱上了这一切

392
00:32:00,970 --> 00:32:02,570
Every bit of it.
书中的一切

393
00:32:02,770 --> 00:32:06,170
The truth, the justice, the bravery,
真理 正义 勇气...

394
00:32:06,470 --> 00:32:08,170
the sword-fighting.
剑斗

395
00:32:10,270 --> 00:32:13,170
He even loved things you wouldn't suspect.
他甚至爱上了你料想不到的东西

396
00:32:14,170 --> 00:32:16,470
The story said she was a prisoner,
故事中她是一名囚徒

397
00:32:16,570 --> 00:32:18,770
but that wasn't totally true
但那并非完全属实

398
00:32:18,870 --> 00:32:22,770
because she had hope, and whenever you have hope,
因为她还抱着希望 而只要心怀希望

399
00:32:22,870 --> 00:32:25,070
you're never really anybody's prisoner.
任何人都不可能正真囚禁你

400
00:32:25,670 --> 00:32:27,770
Someday, my prince will come.
有一天 我的王子会出现

401
00:32:28,370 --> 00:32:30,470
But how did she know that?
但她又怎么知道呢?

402
00:32:30,670 --> 00:32:32,870
Yeah, how did she know that?
是啊 她怎么知道?

403
00:33:21,070 --> 00:33:22,570
Why are you crying?
你为什么哭?

404
00:33:24,970 --> 00:33:26,770
Why are you crying?
你为什么哭?

405
00:33:28,270 --> 00:33:29,870
Down here.
我在这下面

406
00:33:30,170 --> 00:33:31,470
Are you a rat?
你是只耗子?

407
00:33:31,870 --> 00:33:32,970
No.
不

408
00:33:32,970 --> 00:33:34,670
What are you? A mouse?
那你是什么? 老鼠?

409
00:33:37,670 --> 00:33:39,070
I am a gentleman.
我是位绅士

410
00:33:42,070 --> 00:33:43,570
And how do you do?
你好啊

411
00:33:46,070 --> 00:33:47,070
You're sad.
你很难过

412
00:33:47,970 --> 00:33:48,970
Yes.
是的

413
00:33:49,370 --> 00:33:50,370
Because you have longing.
因为你有渴望

414
00:33:52,670 --> 00:33:54,170
You're a strange little mouse.
你是只奇怪的小老鼠

415
00:33:54,970 --> 00:33:55,970
Thank you.
谢谢

416
00:33:59,670 --> 00:34:00,970
Come on.
过来

417
00:34:09,070 --> 00:34:10,470
Where did you hear that?
你从哪听来的?

418
00:34:11,370 --> 00:34:12,970
About the longing.
关于渴望

419
00:34:12,970 --> 00:34:14,370
In a story.
从一个故事里

420
00:34:14,470 --> 00:34:16,470
A story? About what?
故事? 讲什么的?

421
00:34:16,970 --> 00:34:19,670
About a princess, like you, in a castle, like this.
讲一个公主 就像你 在一座城堡里 就像这里

422
00:34:20,770 --> 00:34:23,770
Oh. You're a smooth little mouse, aren't you?
哦 你真是个能说会道的小老鼠

423
00:34:24,970 --> 00:34:27,470
Bet you tell that to all the princesses.
我打赌你对所有的公主都这么说

424
00:34:27,870 --> 00:34:29,670
I am sworn to tell the truth.
我发誓只讲真话

425
00:34:29,970 --> 00:34:31,370
It is a code of honor.
这是种诚信准则

426
00:34:31,470 --> 00:34:36,270
Ah. Not just a gentleman, an honorable gentleman.
噢 你不仅是位绅士 还是位可敬的绅士

427
00:34:37,670 --> 00:34:40,370
Well, then, how does this story end
那么 故事结局是什么呢?

428
00:34:40,470 --> 00:34:42,670
with this princess who's locked in a castle?
那个被囚禁在城堡的公主

429
00:34:42,770 --> 00:34:44,170
I don't know...
我不知道...

430
00:34:44,470 --> 00:34:45,970
I haven't finished it yet.
我还没有读完

431
00:34:47,070 --> 00:34:48,470
I'd love to know.
我想知道

432
00:34:49,470 --> 00:34:51,470
Oh, I wish it would rain.
哦 我希望能下场雨

433
00:34:51,870 --> 00:34:54,070
I wish there was soup again.
我希望能再喝到汤

434
00:34:54,170 --> 00:34:56,370
I even wish there were rats!
我甚至希望还有耗子!

435
00:34:57,570 --> 00:34:59,270
Will you promise me that?
你可以答应我吗?

436
00:34:59,370 --> 00:35:01,870
Will you promise to finish your story and tell me how it ends?
答应我看完故事 告诉我结局?

437
00:35:02,470 --> 00:35:04,870
Yes. It will be my quest.
好的 这将是我的追求

438
00:35:05,870 --> 00:35:09,270
Your quest! You are a very brave mouse.
你的追求! 你真是只勇敢的小老鼠

439
00:35:15,670 --> 00:35:17,870
Thank you, my good gentleman.
谢谢你 我的好绅士

440
00:35:53,270 --> 00:35:56,670
Now, there are all kinds of princesses.
世界上有各种各样的公主

441
00:35:58,370 --> 00:36:00,270
Some are born that way,
一些出生就是公主

442
00:36:00,370 --> 00:36:02,070
some marry into it,
一些是嫁给了王子

443
00:36:02,370 --> 00:36:05,970
and some are destined to be princesses
而还有一些 却只有在自己的想象中

444
00:36:06,070 --> 00:36:07,470
only in their own minds.
才能成为公主

445
00:36:09,170 --> 00:36:10,870
But at one time or another,
但总有那么些时候

446
00:36:10,970 --> 00:36:13,970
every little girl longs to be a princess.
每个小女孩都希望成为公主

447
00:36:16,270 --> 00:36:17,970
I'm gonna live right there.
我以后就要住在那儿

448
00:36:18,070 --> 00:36:20,970
Right up there, near the tippy-top.
就在那 就在那尖顶上

449
00:36:22,270 --> 00:36:25,570
Quit your daydreaming and feed those swine!
少做白日梦了 快喂猪!

450
00:36:26,270 --> 00:36:28,870
Yes, I know. It's gonna be all mine.
我知道 总有一天那会是我的

451
00:36:29,670 --> 00:36:34,570
No, you deaf little urchin. I said feed those swine!
你这丫头聋啦 我说了 快 喂 猪!

452
00:36:38,270 --> 00:36:40,470
Miggery Sow had been shoveling slop
在Miggery Sow的记忆中

453
00:36:40,470 --> 00:36:42,470
for as long as she could remember.
她已经铲猪食好多年了

454
00:36:42,870 --> 00:36:46,770
Her Uncle Ned had put a shovel in her hand from the minute she could hold one.
她刚拿得动铲子 他叔叔Ned就逼她干活

455
00:36:47,370 --> 00:36:49,370
But it turned out all right
但是结果还不错

456
00:36:49,470 --> 00:36:51,470
because she got on quite nicely with the pigs.
因为她和小猪处的很好

457
00:36:51,570 --> 00:36:52,970
That's right.
没错

458
00:36:53,270 --> 00:36:57,170
I'm gonna have a special room just for my dresses
我会有一整间房间专门放衣服

459
00:36:57,470 --> 00:37:01,070
and another whole closet just for my knickers!
还有一个大衣橱 专门放我的短裤!

460
00:37:01,170 --> 00:37:05,070
In fact, Miggery Sow could see her future so clearly.
事实上 Miggery Sow 可以清晰的看到她的未来

461
00:37:05,670 --> 00:37:09,670
She could see the tiara, the fancy dresses, the maids-in-waiting,
她可以看到皇冠 漂亮裙子 还有仕女

462
00:37:10,570 --> 00:37:13,470
and when things got really bad around the farm,
而当农场生活难以忍受的时候

463
00:37:13,570 --> 00:37:17,970
she could see the moment that she would finally be delivered from all of this.
她还能看到 她从这一切中解脱的时刻

464
00:37:18,470 --> 00:37:19,870
Not long now.
不会太久的

465
00:37:19,870 --> 00:37:21,570
I promise you that.
我发誓

466
00:37:22,070 --> 00:37:26,670
20 for the big ones, 15 for the sow, and 12 for the girl.
大的20 母猪15 女孩12

467
00:37:27,170 --> 00:37:29,770
15 for the girl, same as the sow.
女孩15 和母猪一个价

468
00:37:31,170 --> 00:37:34,870
I told you! I told you I'd make it to the castle!
我说过的 我说过的! 我要去城堡了!

469
00:37:34,970 --> 00:37:36,470
Whoa!
哦噢

470
00:37:38,070 --> 00:37:41,270
So sometimes, it doesn't take much for your dreams to come true.
所以有时候 梦想成真并不难

471
00:37:42,270 --> 00:37:45,170
You just have to be able to see it that way.
只要你能够这么认为

472
00:37:45,970 --> 00:37:49,370
She was beautiful! Like an angel.
她真漂亮 就像一个天使

473
00:37:49,970 --> 00:37:51,570
You are crazy.
你疯了

474
00:37:51,770 --> 00:37:54,470
And she smelled so amazing.
她的气味真好闻

475
00:37:55,070 --> 00:37:56,170
Like a garden.
像花园

476
00:37:56,670 --> 00:37:57,770
Despereaux!
Despereaux!

477
00:37:57,770 --> 00:37:59,770
You can't talk to a human.
你不能和人类说话

478
00:37:59,870 --> 00:38:01,370
That is the worst thing you can do.
这是你最不该做的事

479
00:38:01,470 --> 00:38:03,370
No, it's the best thing I ever did.
不 这是我做过的最棒的事

480
00:38:03,570 --> 00:38:04,870
They will throw you in the dungeon.
他们会把你关进地牢

481
00:38:04,970 --> 00:38:06,570
You will get eaten by rats!
你会被耗子吃了

482
00:38:06,570 --> 00:38:07,870
It would be worth it.
就算这样也值得

483
00:38:08,270 --> 00:38:10,270
They could tear at my flesh.
他们可以把我撕裂

484
00:38:10,370 --> 00:38:11,770
Oh, this is bad.
哦 太糟了

485
00:38:11,770 --> 00:38:14,270
Oh, and when she held me in her hand, it was...
哦 当她把我托在手里...

486
00:38:14,770 --> 00:38:18,170
It was so soft, like floating in a pillow.
是那么柔软 就好像漂在云端

487
00:38:18,570 --> 00:38:19,970
You know what? I'm worried about you.
你知道吗? 我很担心你

488
00:38:20,270 --> 00:38:21,970
That's the point, Furlough.
这就是重点 Furlough

489
00:38:22,070 --> 00:38:23,870
There's nothing to be afraid of.
根本没什么好怕的

490
00:38:23,970 --> 00:38:25,870
Quiet! They will hear you.
轻点! 他们会听到的

491
00:38:25,970 --> 00:38:27,770
Come on. Just try it.
来吧 你应该试试

492
00:38:28,070 --> 00:38:30,770
Just for a second, just try being brave.
就这么一会儿 试着变勇敢些

493
00:38:30,970 --> 00:38:32,770
- Oh! - And stop cowering!
- 哦! - 别再害怕了!

494
00:38:32,870 --> 00:38:35,170
What's going on in here?
这是怎么回事?

495
00:38:35,170 --> 00:38:39,870
What's all this talk about princesses and bravery?
你们为什么在说什么公主 ...什么勇敢?

496
00:38:40,870 --> 00:38:43,470
Furlough, I want to see you in my study, right now.
Furlough 你到我的书房来 马上

497
00:38:47,070 --> 00:38:49,270
Are you sure? - That's what he said.
- 你确定? - 他就是这么说的

498
00:38:49,370 --> 00:38:51,770
- A real human? - A princess.
- 一个人类? - 一个公主

499
00:38:53,470 --> 00:38:54,570
We need to tell them.
我们得告诉他们

500
00:38:54,670 --> 00:38:56,170
We need to tell the Mouse Council.
我们得告诉老鼠议会

501
00:38:56,370 --> 00:38:58,670
- But they'll... - This is bad. This is very bad.
- 但是他们会... - 太糟了 真是太糟糕了

502
00:38:58,670 --> 00:39:01,670
If they find out... If they find out that they didn't find out...
如果他们发现 如果他们发现了 他们没有发现的...

503
00:39:01,770 --> 00:39:04,870
Oh, then they'll find out that it was me who...
哦 他们会发现的 是我...

504
00:39:04,870 --> 00:39:05,970
Oh, no.
哦 不

505
00:39:06,070 --> 00:39:08,270
But they will send him to the dungeon!
可他们会把他关进地牢的!

506
00:39:08,670 --> 00:39:11,170
- Oh, he'll get eaten by rats! - Oh!
- 哦 他会被耗子吃了! - 哦!

507
00:39:11,270 --> 00:39:12,770
No, not if we beg.
不 如果我们恳求的话就不会

508
00:39:12,870 --> 00:39:16,870
If we really beg and show them that he's changed.
如果我们真心地恳求 告诉他们他在改变

509
00:39:17,270 --> 00:39:18,670
That he's afraid.
他会害怕

510
00:39:18,670 --> 00:39:22,170
That he's afraid, and he's turned into a real mouse.
他会害怕 然后他会变成一只正的老鼠

511
00:39:22,970 --> 00:39:24,370
Despereaux!
Despereaux!

512
00:39:33,970 --> 00:39:36,470
Of course, destiny is a funny thing.
当然 命运很有意思

513
00:39:37,070 --> 00:39:40,770
We go out to meet it, and we don't always know that we are.
我们出去和它相遇 但有时我们并不自知

514
00:39:50,270 --> 00:39:51,870
For glory and honor!
为荣耀和自豪!

515
00:39:51,970 --> 00:39:53,370
Surround him!
包围他!

516
00:40:10,970 --> 00:40:12,270
Despereaux Tilling.
Despereaux Tilling

517
00:40:15,370 --> 00:40:18,270
How long have you been working on this book?
你读这本书多久了?

518
00:40:18,270 --> 00:40:20,270
Hmm... A week?
恩...一个礼拜?

519
00:40:20,370 --> 00:40:22,670
A week? You've hardly cracked it.
一周? 你毫无悔意嘛

520
00:40:23,470 --> 00:40:24,970
Well, I was...
恩 我只是...

521
00:40:26,270 --> 00:40:28,070
I just wanted to see how it ends.
我只是想知道结局

522
00:40:38,870 --> 00:40:40,970
Refused training as a mouse.
拒绝接受老鼠的教育

523
00:40:40,970 --> 00:40:44,470
Refused to respect the will and guidance of elder mice.
无视长者的意愿和教诲

524
00:40:44,870 --> 00:40:48,570
Repeatedly engaged in bold and un-meek behavior.
一再做出胆大妄为的行为

525
00:40:48,670 --> 00:40:54,770
Triggered willfully not less than 17 mousetraps.
蓄意触发至少17个老鼠夹

526
00:40:54,970 --> 00:40:55,970
Just shameful!
真是可耻!

527
00:40:56,070 --> 00:40:58,270
Had personal contact with...
私自接触...

528
00:40:58,970 --> 00:41:00,070
With...
接触...

529
00:41:03,070 --> 00:41:04,170
With a human being.
接触人类

530
00:41:06,170 --> 00:41:08,270
Isn't there something you can do?
你不能做点什么吗?

531
00:41:08,370 --> 00:41:10,470
Antoinette, stop right now! Stop that.
Antoinette 别说了! 别说了

532
00:41:10,570 --> 00:41:11,970
You have to trust them.
你必须信任他们

533
00:41:12,070 --> 00:41:13,670
They are the Council.
他们是议会

534
00:41:13,670 --> 00:41:15,870
They're the Council because...
他们是议会是因为...

535
00:41:16,170 --> 00:41:18,670
Because they're the Council.
因为...他们...是议会

536
00:41:20,370 --> 00:41:21,770
They're the Council.
他们是议会

537
00:41:22,470 --> 00:41:24,170
Is there anything you wish to say in your defense?
你还有什么想为自己辩护的吗?

538
00:41:25,170 --> 00:41:28,970
Well, it was a very good story,
恩 那是个很棒的故事

539
00:41:29,870 --> 00:41:33,770
and she was a very beautiful princess.
她是一个很美的公主

540
00:41:36,070 --> 00:41:38,070
Despereaux Tilling,
Despereaux Tilling

541
00:41:38,070 --> 00:41:41,670
our laws are here to protect us and our way of life.
我们的法律旨在保护我们 以及我们的生活方式

542
00:41:42,370 --> 00:41:45,870
And when one of our citizens strays from that way of life,
当我们中有人偏离了这种生活方式

543
00:41:46,270 --> 00:41:48,470
he becomes a threat to us all.
他就会成为我们大家的威胁

544
00:41:49,070 --> 00:41:50,970
It's an easy question.
问题很简单

545
00:41:51,870 --> 00:41:54,270
Are you a man or are you a mouse?
你是人 还是老鼠?

546
00:41:57,370 --> 00:41:58,670
And your actions have told us
你的行为已经告诉了我们

547
00:41:58,770 --> 00:42:01,770
that you have a great deal of trouble being a mouse.
要你做只老鼠很困难

548
00:42:03,170 --> 00:42:05,070
It is the judgment of this court
议会现在判决

549
00:42:05,170 --> 00:42:07,770
that you should be banished from these walls forever.
你将被永远流放

550
00:42:08,370 --> 00:42:12,170
You shall be remanded into the custody of Hovis, the Threadmaster,
线绳大师Hovis会押送你

551
00:42:12,270 --> 00:42:15,570
who will prepare you for your descent into the dungeons of Dor,
把你送去多尔国的地牢

552
00:42:15,670 --> 00:42:19,670
from which no mouse and no light has ever escaped.
在那里 从没有一只老鼠逃脱 从没有一丝光明泄漏

553
00:42:31,270 --> 00:42:33,470
- Shh! - My baby!
- 嘘! - 我的孩子!

554
00:42:33,570 --> 00:42:37,170
Quiet. Be quiet, my dear. There's nothing to be done.
安静 亲爱的 这也是没办法的事

555
00:43:02,770 --> 00:43:04,170
Come with me.
跟我走

556
00:43:12,570 --> 00:43:13,970
Stand there.
站在那

557
00:43:25,370 --> 00:43:26,370
Red?
红色?

558
00:43:26,670 --> 00:43:28,670
Ah, so they tell me.
啊 他们是这么告诉我的

559
00:43:30,970 --> 00:43:32,970
So you're the brave one.
你是只勇敢的老鼠

560
00:43:34,070 --> 00:43:35,170
I guess.
也许吧

561
00:43:35,270 --> 00:43:37,870
It's good. It'll carry well down there.
好了 会安全把你放下去

562
00:43:39,570 --> 00:43:41,170
Wear it proudly.
为你的勇敢骄傲吧

563
00:43:41,970 --> 00:43:43,570
There's no shame.
没什么好羞耻的

564
00:43:46,370 --> 00:43:47,670
It's time.
到时间了

565
00:43:50,570 --> 00:43:53,870
It's all right. They're too scared to come down here.
没什么的 他们都太胆小不敢下去

566
00:44:00,270 --> 00:44:01,570
In there?
这里?

567
00:44:01,870 --> 00:44:03,370
I'm afraid so.
我恐怕是的

568
00:44:05,270 --> 00:44:06,770
Courage, right?
勇气 对吗?

569
00:44:06,870 --> 00:44:08,170
And truth.
还有真理

570
00:44:08,770 --> 00:44:10,770
- And honor. - Good.
- 还有荣誉 - 很好

571
00:44:10,870 --> 00:44:13,370
But especially courage.
但特别要有勇气

572
00:44:25,270 --> 00:44:26,270
I'm ready.
我准备好了

573
00:44:26,370 --> 00:44:28,370
All right, then you need to...
好吧 然后你要...

574
00:45:06,270 --> 00:45:07,770
What? Whoa!
什么? 哇!

575
00:46:03,970 --> 00:46:06,970
Hello? Hello?
哈喽? 哈喽?

576
00:46:09,670 --> 00:46:10,670
Whoa!
哇哦

577
00:46:14,570 --> 00:46:15,870
Lads, let's go, on the double!
小的们 撤 赶紧地!

578
00:46:19,670 --> 00:46:20,770
Who is that?
谁?

579
00:46:21,270 --> 00:46:22,670
Who goes there?
谁在那儿?

580
00:46:23,570 --> 00:46:24,770
Who is that?
谁啊?

581
00:46:24,870 --> 00:46:26,370
Despereaux Tilling.
Despereaux Tilling

582
00:46:26,470 --> 00:46:28,670
Are you a man or are you a mouse?
你是人 还是老鼠?

583
00:46:30,570 --> 00:46:33,170
I am a gentleman.
我是绅士

584
00:46:33,570 --> 00:46:35,070
Oh.
哦

585
00:46:36,670 --> 00:46:38,170
- It's a mouse. - I'm hungry.
- 是只老鼠 - 我饿了

586
00:46:38,370 --> 00:46:41,370
Shh! Quiet, lads. Patience.
嘘! 安静 小的们 耐心点

587
00:46:42,670 --> 00:46:45,170
And what makes you a gentleman?
是什么让你成了绅士的?

588
00:46:45,770 --> 00:46:46,970
A code...
诚信...

589
00:46:47,070 --> 00:46:48,370
A code of honor.
诚信准则

590
00:46:49,570 --> 00:46:51,670
You're a strange little mouse, aren't you?
你真是只奇怪的小老鼠 对吧?

591
00:46:51,770 --> 00:46:54,270
And where did you find this code of honor?
你从哪儿听来的"诚信准则"?

592
00:46:54,370 --> 00:46:56,270
Well, in a legend.
在一个传说里

593
00:46:56,370 --> 00:46:57,770
A legend that I read.
我读过的一个传说

594
00:46:57,870 --> 00:47:00,570
Fine. Oh, tell me this legend of yours.
好吧 跟说说你那个传说

595
00:47:00,670 --> 00:47:02,970
I could do with a good story right now.
现在听段精彩的故事也不错

596
00:47:03,270 --> 00:47:04,570
Well,
嗯

597
00:47:04,670 --> 00:47:07,070
it's about a princess and a knight
故事讲的是一位公主 和一个骑士

598
00:47:08,270 --> 00:47:10,270
and his quest to save her honor.
还有他捍卫她的荣誉的历程

599
00:47:10,770 --> 00:47:14,070
Ah. It was a princess that took away my soup.
啊 让我喝不了汤的就是个公主

600
00:47:14,570 --> 00:47:16,070
She didn't take it.
不是她干的

601
00:47:16,170 --> 00:47:18,270
In fact, she misses it, too!
实际上 她也想念汤!

602
00:47:19,570 --> 00:47:21,670
How do you know all this, then?
你怎么知道得这么清楚?

603
00:47:21,770 --> 00:47:22,870
I've seen her.
我见过她

604
00:47:23,170 --> 00:47:24,970
- Seen her? - I've talked to her.
- 见过她? - 和她说过话

605
00:47:25,070 --> 00:47:27,470
- Talked to her? - That's why they sent me down here.
- 还说过话? - 所以我被驱逐到这儿来

606
00:47:27,570 --> 00:47:29,870
Mmm-hmm. And what did this princess tell you
嗯 那跟你这个小听众...

607
00:47:29,970 --> 00:47:31,570
when you had your little audience?
公主都说了些啥?

608
00:47:31,670 --> 00:47:33,070
Eh? Eh?
呵?

609
00:47:33,170 --> 00:47:35,970
Oh, you must be a royal mouse. Is that it?
你肯定是只皇室老鼠 是不是?

610
00:47:36,470 --> 00:47:39,970
She told me that she missed the soup and the rain
她说她想念汤 还有雨

611
00:47:40,670 --> 00:47:42,570
and, most of all, the sunlight.
最想念的是阳光

612
00:47:43,370 --> 00:47:45,870
And that she just wanted it all to come back again.
她希望这一切都能重新回来

613
00:47:49,370 --> 00:47:50,870
Well, I don't want to hear your little stories
我不想听你的故事了

614
00:47:50,970 --> 00:47:52,970
about princesses and sunshine.
什么公主啊阳光的

615
00:47:53,870 --> 00:47:55,770
Go tell them to the rats!
还是和耗子们说去吧!

616
00:48:02,370 --> 00:48:03,670
All right, boys, come on!
好 孩儿们 上啊!

617
00:48:44,170 --> 00:48:45,470
Good crowd, isn't it, sir?
观众很多 是吧 先生?

618
00:48:46,070 --> 00:48:48,170
Yes, it is, quite.
没错 的确很多

619
00:48:48,170 --> 00:48:50,370
Mouse! Mouse! Mouse! Mouse!
老鼠! 老鼠! 老鼠! 老鼠!

620
00:48:57,370 --> 00:49:00,670
Ah, Roscuro! I'm glad you could make it.
哦 Roscuro! 很高兴你也来了

621
00:49:00,770 --> 00:49:03,270
I thought you didn't like the arena.
我还以为你不喜欢竞技场呢

622
00:49:03,370 --> 00:49:06,470
Huh? Oh! No, no. It... It's an honor, sir.
哦 不 不 很荣幸能来这里 先生

623
00:49:07,170 --> 00:49:08,170
Oh!
哦

624
00:49:08,270 --> 00:49:09,470
- Good. - Mmm.
- 很好 - 嗯

625
00:49:09,670 --> 00:49:11,670
Well, enjoy.
来吧 尽情享受

626
00:49:12,170 --> 00:49:15,170
Oh, uh... Thank you.
哦 呃...谢谢

627
00:49:20,170 --> 00:49:22,170
Let the games begin!
游戏开始!

628
00:49:35,470 --> 00:49:38,170
Mouse! Mouse! Mouse!
老鼠! 老鼠! 老鼠!

629
00:49:56,970 --> 00:49:57,970
Come on!
上啊

630
00:50:41,470 --> 00:50:42,470
Hold on!
抓紧了!

631
00:50:48,870 --> 00:50:51,170
Eat! Eat! Eat!
吃了他! 吃了他! 吃了他!

632
00:51:01,070 --> 00:51:02,170
Wait!
等等!

633
00:51:02,470 --> 00:51:06,270
Can I have him? Can I have this one? Please?
能把他给我吗? 求你了

634
00:51:09,970 --> 00:51:10,970
What?
什么?

635
00:51:11,370 --> 00:51:14,670
It's just that that one looks tasty.
就是 他看起来...很好吃的样子

636
00:51:14,870 --> 00:51:17,470
Well, this is progress.
有进步了嘛

637
00:51:17,570 --> 00:51:21,570
Perhaps we're starting to leave the past behind us, eh?
也许我们应该尽释前嫌 呃?

638
00:51:21,770 --> 00:51:24,170
Enjoy, my friend.
好好享用 我的朋友

639
00:51:24,270 --> 00:51:26,570
Don't leave a morsel.
一口都不要剩

640
00:51:26,670 --> 00:51:28,970
Oh, I won't.
哦 我不会的

641
00:51:30,970 --> 00:51:31,970
Pull!
拉回来!

642
00:51:48,370 --> 00:51:50,770
Come on, let's go, buster!
动作快点 我们走 小鬼!

643
00:51:51,170 --> 00:51:54,170
That's it. That's it. You keep moving!
就这样 就这样 快给我走!

644
00:51:56,270 --> 00:51:59,070
It's okay. Keep walking.
没事的 继续往前走

645
00:51:59,370 --> 00:52:02,870
Come on, keep moving! Let's go, come on!
快点 往前走! 快!

646
00:52:04,870 --> 00:52:06,270
It's right up there.
就在那上面

647
00:52:14,370 --> 00:52:15,970
- Huh? - Keep walking.
继续往前走

648
00:52:23,670 --> 00:52:25,070
- Oh. - See that?
- 哦 - 看见没?

649
00:52:26,070 --> 00:52:27,970
Light. Real light.
光 真正的光

650
00:52:29,470 --> 00:52:31,870
It's mine, but you can share it.
这是我的 不过你也可以分享

651
00:52:32,570 --> 00:52:36,570
It isn't much, but there isn't much anywhere since everything turned gray.
不是很多 但世界变得灰暗后 哪儿都没有很多的光了

652
00:52:38,570 --> 00:52:40,270
You're not gonna eat me?
你不吃我?

653
00:52:40,670 --> 00:52:42,870
No. I don't eat mice.
不 我不吃老鼠

654
00:52:43,270 --> 00:52:44,670
Then what do you eat?
那你吃啥?

655
00:52:44,970 --> 00:52:46,070
Crumbs.
面包屑

656
00:52:46,170 --> 00:52:47,470
When I can find them.
如果能找到的话

657
00:52:48,970 --> 00:52:51,270
So you are a gentleman.
这么说 你是绅士

658
00:52:54,070 --> 00:52:55,670
Tell me that story.
跟我说说那个故事

659
00:52:56,570 --> 00:52:58,070
About the Princess.
公主的故事

660
00:52:58,870 --> 00:53:00,770
Tell me what she looked like.
说说她什么样儿

661
00:53:01,270 --> 00:53:03,070
Well, she was...
呃 她...

662
00:53:03,170 --> 00:53:04,470
Was she angry?
她有没有生气?

663
00:53:04,570 --> 00:53:05,770
No.
没有

664
00:53:05,870 --> 00:53:07,570
No, not at all.
一点都没有

665
00:53:07,570 --> 00:53:10,570
Her heart was full of longing.
她内心充满了...渴望

666
00:53:12,170 --> 00:53:13,770
What's longing?
什么是渴望?

667
00:53:15,670 --> 00:53:18,570
And that's how a friendship is born.
一段友谊就这样诞生了

668
00:53:19,270 --> 00:53:23,270
Over the next few weeks, he told Roscuro everything he knew about loyalty
接下来的几个星期里 他把他知道的都告诉了Roscuro

669
00:53:23,370 --> 00:53:25,770
and honor and chivalry and courage.
忠诚 荣誉 侠义和勇气

670
00:53:25,770 --> 00:53:29,170
He told him about the Princess, and where her longing came from.
他说了公主的事 说到她为什么会有渴望

671
00:53:29,270 --> 00:53:33,070
That she missed the rain and the soup and even the rats.
说到她想念雨水 汤汁 甚至是耗子

672
00:53:34,370 --> 00:53:35,470
Even the rats?
甚至是耗子?

673
00:53:36,170 --> 00:53:40,170
He told him about their code of honor, about his noble quest,
他跟他说了诚信准则 说了他高尚的追求

674
00:53:40,770 --> 00:53:43,070
about duty and loyalty.
说到了责任和忠诚

675
00:53:43,670 --> 00:53:46,770
And there, in the darkness of the cellar,
就在这个黑暗的地牢里

676
00:53:46,770 --> 00:53:51,970
two knights pledged devotion to a princess who was trapped inside a castle.
两位骑士许下郑重承诺 要解救困在堡垒中的公主

677
00:53:53,270 --> 00:53:55,770
Trapped in a life full of pain and longing.
公主的生活充满痛苦和渴望

678
00:53:55,870 --> 00:53:57,770
Even if no one could tell.
哪怕没有人知道

679
00:54:01,970 --> 00:54:03,770
Your crown, ma'am.
您的王冠 殿下

680
00:54:04,970 --> 00:54:06,070
Oh.
哦

681
00:54:07,170 --> 00:54:08,770
I don't want it today.
我今天不想戴

682
00:54:08,770 --> 00:54:10,570
But it's beautiful, ma'am.
但它多漂亮啊 殿下

683
00:54:10,970 --> 00:54:13,070
I know, but I don't want it.
我知道 但我今天不想戴

684
00:54:13,170 --> 00:54:15,770
You look so pretty in it, ma'am.
你戴上很好看的 殿下

685
00:54:15,870 --> 00:54:17,770
Like a princess.
就象公主一样

686
00:54:17,970 --> 00:54:20,970
I know. I am the princess.
我知道 我就是公主

687
00:54:21,270 --> 00:54:22,770
Oh, I know, ma'am,
我知道的 殿下

688
00:54:22,970 --> 00:54:26,970
but such a fine princess, with a little, pretty, glittery...
不过 这么漂亮的公主 戴上这个美丽闪耀的小皇冠...

689
00:54:27,170 --> 00:54:28,770
I don't want it!
我不想戴!

690
00:54:28,970 --> 00:54:30,370
All right, Mig?
行不行 Mig?

691
00:54:31,370 --> 00:54:32,970
Very well, ma'am.
好的 殿下

692
00:54:33,570 --> 00:54:35,270
Please, take it away.
请把它拿走

693
00:54:52,370 --> 00:54:53,370
Princess.
公主

694
00:54:54,470 --> 00:54:55,970
Who's the princess?
谁是公主?

695
00:54:56,670 --> 00:54:58,270
I'm a princess.
我是公主

696
00:54:58,370 --> 00:55:00,270
I'm the princess.
我才是公主

697
00:55:02,170 --> 00:55:06,970
My comb, my hat, my gloves
我的梳子 我的王冠 我的手套

698
00:55:07,970 --> 00:55:11,970
and my pretty powder
还有我美丽的粉扑

699
00:55:12,070 --> 00:55:14,670
on my pretty princess face.
扑在我美丽的公主脸蛋上

700
00:55:14,770 --> 00:55:16,970
And what do you think you're doing?
你在做什么?

701
00:55:17,070 --> 00:55:18,070
Ma'am!
夫人!

702
00:55:18,170 --> 00:55:20,770
Where did you get all this?
你从哪儿拿的这些东西?

703
00:55:20,870 --> 00:55:22,670
I just borrowed it, ma'am.
我借来的 夫人

704
00:55:22,770 --> 00:55:23,870
Borrowed it?
借来的?

705
00:55:24,170 --> 00:55:26,270
I was gonna put them all back.
我会还回去的

706
00:55:26,370 --> 00:55:27,670
See that you do!
看看你做的好事!

707
00:55:29,170 --> 00:55:32,070
And you can spend the whole week
这个礼拜

708
00:55:32,170 --> 00:55:33,970
taking slop to the dungeon
你就去地牢里送饭吧

709
00:55:34,070 --> 00:55:36,170
for your little escapade.
居然做出这种事

710
00:55:37,070 --> 00:55:38,370
"Princess"!
还"公主"呢!

711
00:55:42,070 --> 00:55:44,970
God! She's the princess.
上帝啊! 她才是公主

712
00:55:46,170 --> 00:55:50,870
And now I have to carry the sloppy, gloppy, stinky stew
而我只能端着又油又脏又臭的餐盘

713
00:55:50,870 --> 00:55:53,570
down in the damp, dark, dingy...
来这个又湿又黑又破的...

714
00:55:55,870 --> 00:55:58,170
A person could get lost forever down here.
在这儿还真容易迷路啊

715
00:56:03,070 --> 00:56:04,070
Din-din.
叮叮

716
00:56:05,570 --> 00:56:06,570
Slop.
上饭

717
00:56:09,070 --> 00:56:12,670
No, don't stop! I said "slop"!
不 别傻站着! 我说让你上饭!

718
00:56:17,670 --> 00:56:20,070
How am I supposed to eat this swill?
这种猪食让我怎么吃?

719
00:56:21,070 --> 00:56:24,370
Oh, stop that! I don't have to be putting up with all this!
别这样! 我没必要看你脸色!

720
00:56:25,870 --> 00:56:27,570
I serve the Princess.
我是伺候公主的

721
00:56:29,770 --> 00:56:32,470
Right. You serve the Princess.
是啊 你是伺候公主的

722
00:56:32,570 --> 00:56:35,470
- That's a bit of a laugh, isn't it? - I do.
- 真搞笑 是不是? - 是真的

723
00:56:35,570 --> 00:56:38,270
- I bring her tea and... - Well, I don't want to hear it!
- 我给她端茶... - 我才不要听!

724
00:56:39,170 --> 00:56:41,170
Had me own little princess once.
以前我也有个小公主的

725
00:56:41,670 --> 00:56:42,870
And now I don't.
现在没了

726
00:56:43,370 --> 00:56:45,970
Oh. What, you had a princess?
哦 你有个公主?

727
00:56:47,870 --> 00:56:48,870
Yeah.
是啊

728
00:56:48,970 --> 00:56:51,270
Every dad's got a princess.
每个做爸爸的都有个小公主

729
00:56:51,970 --> 00:56:54,070
Till he stops being a dad, of course.
当然 直到他不能再做爸爸

730
00:56:57,070 --> 00:56:59,870
Sorry. So, so, sorry!
对不起 真的真的对不起!

731
00:57:01,570 --> 00:57:03,470
Oh, well, I've got a real one.
我可是有个真正的公主

732
00:57:03,570 --> 00:57:06,670
And she's got a tiara and fancy robes,
她有王冠 漂亮的礼服

733
00:57:06,770 --> 00:57:09,470
and she's got shiny bits all over every frock in her closet.
她衣橱里每件衣服都亮闪闪的

734
00:57:09,670 --> 00:57:12,470
And I get to see her every single day.
而且我每天都能见到她

735
00:57:13,570 --> 00:57:15,170
What kind of a quest?
你的追求是什么?

736
00:57:15,270 --> 00:57:16,270
Uh...
呃...

737
00:57:17,070 --> 00:57:18,870
To right a terrible wrong.
去弥补一个严重的错误

738
00:57:19,370 --> 00:57:21,270
But who did you wrong?
你的错误害了谁?

739
00:57:24,170 --> 00:57:25,170
Okay.
好吧

740
00:57:26,770 --> 00:57:29,470
Do you remember when they banished the rats?
你还记得耗子被驱逐的事吗?

741
00:57:29,970 --> 00:57:31,670
- Sure. Yes. - Okay.
- 当然记得 - 好

742
00:57:32,470 --> 00:57:34,470
Well, it wasn't all the rats they banished.
不是所有的耗子都应该被驱逐

743
00:57:34,570 --> 00:57:38,970
I mean, they did, but it was all because of one particular rat
那都是一只耗子惹的祸

744
00:57:39,770 --> 00:57:41,370
in particular.
全是因为它

745
00:57:44,870 --> 00:57:46,570
If I could just tell her I'm sorry,
如果我能向她道歉

746
00:57:46,670 --> 00:57:51,070
that I'm, you know, I'm really sorry.
告诉她 我真的很抱歉

747
00:57:51,170 --> 00:57:53,870
And that I didn't mean for any of this to happen.
我不想事情变成这样子

748
00:57:53,870 --> 00:57:55,870
If she could just hear me say it,
如果她能听我说

749
00:57:55,870 --> 00:57:58,370
you know, just... Just hear my voice,
只要听听我的声音

750
00:57:58,470 --> 00:58:01,670
she would know how much I meant it.
她就会知道我是多么诚恳

751
00:58:03,570 --> 00:58:05,370
That is a very noble quest.
这是个非常高尚的追求

752
00:58:20,770 --> 00:58:23,170
Your Highness?
殿下?

753
00:58:26,070 --> 00:58:27,970
Your Highness?
殿下?

754
00:58:29,070 --> 00:58:30,570
Is that you?
是你吗?

755
00:58:30,870 --> 00:58:32,170
My little mouse?
我的小老鼠?

756
00:58:32,870 --> 00:58:34,770
Oh, I'm not a mouse. I...
哦 我不是老鼠 我...

757
00:58:35,270 --> 00:58:36,670
I'm a...
我是...

758
00:58:39,670 --> 00:58:40,870
I forgot.
我忘了

759
00:58:41,070 --> 00:58:43,370
You're my little gentleman, aren't you?
你是我的小绅士 是不是?

760
00:58:46,470 --> 00:58:48,470
Have you come to tell me how the story ends?
你是来告诉我故事的结局吗?

761
00:58:48,570 --> 00:58:50,270
Did you finish your quest?
你的追求达成了吗?

762
00:58:51,470 --> 00:58:52,970
Where are you?
你在哪儿啊?

763
00:58:54,070 --> 00:58:56,070
I have come to apologize.
我是来道歉的

764
00:58:56,670 --> 00:58:59,170
Oh, you are noble, remember?
哦 你是高尚的 还记得吗?

765
00:59:00,070 --> 00:59:02,270
You have nothing to be sorry about.
你没有什么可道歉的

766
00:59:03,870 --> 00:59:05,270
Oh, but I am.
噢 我有的

767
00:59:08,370 --> 00:59:09,770
I am sorry.
我很抱歉

768
00:59:12,770 --> 00:59:14,670
I know you.
我认识你

769
00:59:14,770 --> 00:59:17,270
- No, no. - Oh, no!
- 别 别 - 不要过来!

770
00:59:17,370 --> 00:59:19,170
No! Please, please listen. Please.
别这样! 请听我说 拜托

771
00:59:19,270 --> 00:59:20,570
- A rat! - Please. I just want to tell you.
- 耗子! - 求你了 我就是想告诉你...

772
00:59:20,670 --> 00:59:22,270
Someone, please!
来人啊!

773
00:59:22,370 --> 00:59:23,570
Listen. It's okay.
听着 没事的

774
00:59:23,770 --> 00:59:26,170
Get it off me! There's a rat in my room!
滚开! 我房间里有只耗子!

775
00:59:26,470 --> 00:59:28,170
Please get him off!
请把它弄走!

776
00:59:33,970 --> 00:59:34,970
What?
什么?

777
00:59:40,870 --> 00:59:41,870
Rat!
耗子!

778
00:59:46,770 --> 00:59:48,770
It's a rat!
是只耗子!

779
00:59:55,770 --> 00:59:57,370
Quick, rush him!
快 追上他!

780
00:59:57,470 --> 00:59:58,470
Get him!
抓住他!

781
00:59:58,670 --> 00:59:59,970
Filthy rodent!
肮脏的耗子!

782
01:00:15,170 --> 01:00:16,770
Where'd he go?
他去哪儿了

783
01:00:57,670 --> 01:01:01,370
What would you do if your own name was a bad word?
如果你的名字是个脏词 你该怎么办?

784
01:01:03,570 --> 01:01:07,070
If John or Beth or Bill was an insult.
如果说John或Beth或Bill是种侮辱

785
01:01:08,670 --> 01:01:12,070
Well, that's how Roscuro came to feel about who he was.
Roscuro觉得自己就是这样

786
01:01:14,170 --> 01:01:18,170
When your heart breaks, it can grow back crooked.
心灵破碎时 它可能会扭曲

787
01:01:19,170 --> 01:01:22,970
It grows back twisted and gnarled and hard.
会变得阴暗 麻木 冷酷

788
01:01:25,270 --> 01:01:28,670
Even as he changed, Roscuro still had longing.
虽然他改变了 Roscuro还有着渴望

789
01:01:29,670 --> 01:01:34,070
But now he just longed for someone whose heart was as hardened as his was.
但现在 他只渴望找到 和他一样铁石心肠的人

790
01:01:35,070 --> 01:01:40,670
Pretty princess. Pretty, pretty princess pie.
美丽的公主 漂亮动人的公主

791
01:01:41,770 --> 01:01:43,770
What a pretty princess!
多么漂亮的公主啊!

792
01:01:45,370 --> 01:01:46,770
My gloves.
我的手套

793
01:01:47,570 --> 01:01:48,870
My comb.
我的梳子

794
01:01:50,070 --> 01:01:52,870
My jewel-y, girly hat,
我镶着宝石的小王冠

795
01:01:53,270 --> 01:01:57,570
all sitting on my princess head.
戴在我的公主头上

796
01:02:00,970 --> 01:02:06,270
Who's the pretty princess pumpkin pie?
谁是美丽的公主?

797
01:02:09,270 --> 01:02:10,270
You are.
你是

798
01:02:10,670 --> 01:02:13,270
Right. I am.
是啊 我是

799
01:02:13,570 --> 01:02:17,270
You are. And you should be dressed in those clothes.
你是 你应该穿上那些漂亮衣服

800
01:02:17,970 --> 01:02:20,770
Quite right. I should.
说得没错 确实应该

801
01:02:20,970 --> 01:02:23,970
Mmm-hmm. And you should lounge in that bed.
嗯 你应该躺在那张公主床上

802
01:02:24,070 --> 01:02:25,270
Lounging.
闲散地躺着

803
01:02:25,370 --> 01:02:29,270
Lounging round, yes, the whole day!
闲散地度过一整天!

804
01:02:29,670 --> 01:02:32,170
And you should be wearing that crown.
而且你应该戴那个王冠

805
01:02:33,070 --> 01:02:34,670
I should be wearing a frown?
我应该皱眉?

806
01:02:34,770 --> 01:02:38,470
No. No, no, no. Not a frown. A crown.
不不 不是皱眉 是王冠

807
01:02:38,570 --> 01:02:41,770
Wow! Can't hear me own self think.
哇 我听见自己在想什么了

808
01:02:44,470 --> 01:02:45,670
- Ah! - Shh!
- 啊! - 嘘!

809
01:02:45,770 --> 01:02:47,770
- Ah! - Shh!
- 啊! - 嘘!

810
01:02:48,470 --> 01:02:49,470
Shh!
- 啊! - 嘘!

811
01:02:49,570 --> 01:02:51,370
- Ah! - Shh!
- 啊! - 嘘!

812
01:02:53,070 --> 01:02:54,570
Who are you?
你是谁?

813
01:02:54,670 --> 01:02:56,270
I'm here to help you.
我是来帮你的

814
01:02:56,270 --> 01:02:58,870
I can't be caught with a real rat in my bunk.
不能让人发现我房间里有耗子

815
01:02:59,370 --> 01:03:01,070
I don't think so.
不能这样

816
01:03:03,170 --> 01:03:05,770
And what if they find you with a painting of the Princess?
如果让人发现你私藏公主画像怎么办?

817
01:03:05,770 --> 01:03:07,770
You think that's as bad as a rat?
你觉得这和窝藏耗子一样糟吗?

818
01:03:08,570 --> 01:03:10,270
I want the same thing you do.
我们有共同的目标

819
01:03:22,170 --> 01:03:23,170
Allo?
谁呀?

820
01:03:28,370 --> 01:03:29,470
What are you doing?
你干嘛呢?

821
01:03:29,670 --> 01:03:30,670
Uh...
呃...

822
01:03:31,670 --> 01:03:33,570
I need it for a baby.
我来为宝宝拿刀

823
01:03:35,470 --> 01:03:37,270
No, not a baby!
不 不是宝宝!

824
01:03:37,770 --> 01:03:38,770
For milady.
是夫人

825
01:03:38,970 --> 01:03:41,670
I mean milady.
我是说夫人

826
01:03:42,370 --> 01:03:43,470
Yes.
是的

827
01:03:43,970 --> 01:03:45,170
To chop apples.
切苹果用的

828
01:03:46,470 --> 01:03:47,870
She'd like some apples.
她想吃苹果

829
01:03:50,570 --> 01:03:51,670
Now turn and leave.
现在转身离开

830
01:03:51,770 --> 01:03:53,670
Now turn and leave.
现在转身离开

831
01:03:56,170 --> 01:03:59,370
No, no! Just turn and leave.
不是! 是让你转身离开

832
01:03:59,570 --> 01:04:01,270
Oh, right. Sorry.
是哦 不好意思

833
01:04:01,870 --> 01:04:02,870
Sorry. Bye.
不好意思 拜

834
01:04:02,970 --> 01:04:06,270
Oh, I can't hear you, see, because deaf, but...
我听不清你说啥 有点耳背

835
01:04:06,370 --> 01:04:07,470
A bit deaf.
一点点而已

836
01:04:10,670 --> 01:04:13,170
You know, hurt is a funny thing.
伤害是件很奇妙的事

837
01:04:13,270 --> 01:04:17,870
The same thing that makes one person angry can put another person into grief.
它能让一个人愤怒 却让另一个人悲伤

838
01:04:17,870 --> 01:04:20,670
Here, take care of me little princess.
来 照顾我的小公主吧

839
01:04:20,870 --> 01:04:22,470
I can't no more.
我再也照顾不了了

840
01:04:22,770 --> 01:04:25,270
Oh, I will. Don't worry.
哦 我会的 别担心

841
01:04:27,370 --> 01:04:28,470
I'm sorry.
对不起

842
01:04:29,170 --> 01:04:32,170
Sorry. So, so sorry!
真的 真的对不起!

843
01:04:35,370 --> 01:04:38,470
Gregory always said that she had too much heart.
Gregory常说她的心眼太多了

844
01:04:38,570 --> 01:04:42,370
And that's why they had to put some of it on the outside.
所以有些得放在看得见的地方

845
01:04:42,370 --> 01:04:43,870
But let's face it.
但事实是

846
01:04:43,870 --> 01:04:46,570
It's hard to see something on your back.
我们很难看见背后长了什么

847
01:04:46,670 --> 01:04:50,670
In fact, you can have a good heart and not even know it.
实际上 你可能有颗善良的心 自己却不知道

848
01:04:50,870 --> 01:04:52,670
You can do this. You know you can.
你做得到的 你知道你行的

849
01:04:53,070 --> 01:04:54,370
I know I can.
我知道我行

850
01:04:54,370 --> 01:04:59,070
She belongs in the dungeon, and you belong in the palace, like a princess.
她应该去地牢 而你应该在宫殿里 就像个公主

851
01:05:04,770 --> 01:05:05,870
What are you doing?
你在干什么?

852
01:05:07,170 --> 01:05:08,370
I'm cleaning, ma'am.
打扫卫生 殿下

853
01:05:09,870 --> 01:05:11,170
With rope?
用绳子打扫?

854
01:05:11,370 --> 01:05:12,370
It helps, ma'am.
用得上的 殿下

855
01:05:12,470 --> 01:05:14,370
Well, stop it. You look ridiculous.
别说了 你看上去真可笑

856
01:05:16,970 --> 01:05:18,070
Sorry, ma'am?
你说什么 殿下?

857
01:05:18,170 --> 01:05:20,770
I said you look ridiculous.
我说 你看上去真可笑

858
01:05:20,870 --> 01:05:24,170
Ridiculous, ridiculous, ridiculous.
可笑 可笑 可笑

859
01:05:26,070 --> 01:05:27,670
- You can't do this, Mig. - Gor.
- 你不能这么做 Mig - 走

860
01:05:27,970 --> 01:05:29,570
Seems I am, ma'am.
我现在不就这么做了么 殿下

861
01:05:29,670 --> 01:05:31,170
You'll get in a terrible amount of trouble.
你会惹上大麻烦的

862
01:05:31,270 --> 01:05:33,170
Don't listen. You're the princess now.
别听她说 现在你是公主

863
01:05:33,270 --> 01:05:34,770
I'm the princess now.
现在我是公主

864
01:05:34,870 --> 01:05:36,570
And you belong in the palace.
你应该住进宫殿

865
01:05:36,670 --> 01:05:38,270
I belong in the palace.
我应该住进宫殿

866
01:05:38,370 --> 01:05:39,470
And she belongs in...
她应该...

867
01:05:39,570 --> 01:05:41,570
No! You can't do this!
不 你不能这么做!

868
01:05:41,670 --> 01:05:44,870
Help! Help! Someone help me!
救命啊! 救命! 谁来救救我!

869
01:05:44,970 --> 01:05:46,970
Help! Help!
救命! 救命! 救救我啊!

870
01:05:47,770 --> 01:05:50,270
Help! Help!
救命! 救命!

871
01:05:59,270 --> 01:06:01,170
Help! Help!
救命! 救命!

872
01:06:03,070 --> 01:06:04,570
Help!
救命!

873
01:06:05,470 --> 01:06:07,270
I'm in here!
我在这儿!

874
01:06:09,270 --> 01:06:10,770
Help!
救命!

875
01:06:11,170 --> 01:06:12,970
You filthy, stinking rat!
你这个肮脏的死耗子!

876
01:06:14,170 --> 01:06:15,570
You tricked me!
你骗了我!

877
01:06:18,570 --> 01:06:19,670
Here's the spot, rats!
就是这儿了 耗子们!

878
01:06:19,670 --> 01:06:21,070
What's Roscuro brought us, then?
Roscuro给我们带什么来了?

879
01:06:21,170 --> 01:06:22,570
Hungry! Yum! Hungry now!
好饿! 好饿啊!

880
01:06:22,670 --> 01:06:24,470
Not yet, lads. No, no, you've got to wait.
现在不行 伙计们 不 再等等

881
01:06:24,570 --> 01:06:25,970
It's nowhere near dinnertime.
离晚饭时间还远着呢

882
01:06:26,070 --> 01:06:28,170
Oh, come on, Smudge, I'm starving.
哦拜托 Smudge 我要饿死了

883
01:06:33,470 --> 01:06:35,870
Something special for dinner tonight.
今晚有美味哦

884
01:06:36,170 --> 01:06:37,670
Smells delicious!
好香!

885
01:06:39,870 --> 01:06:42,970
Smells human to me. A young one. - And not just any human.
- 像是人味儿 年轻人 - 不是一般的人

886
01:06:43,070 --> 01:06:45,070
Let's have a look. - It's the Princess!
- 来看看 - 是个公主!

887
01:06:45,170 --> 01:06:46,970
Oi, you'll wait for your dinner like everyone else.
喂 你得跟别人一样 等到晚饭时间

888
01:06:47,070 --> 01:06:48,170
Come on, Smudge, give us a little look.
拜托 Smudge 让我们看一眼嘛

889
01:06:48,170 --> 01:06:49,270
No, no, no!
不行 不行 不行!

890
01:06:49,370 --> 01:06:51,870
Boss doesn't want her getting nervous. Spoils the meat, doesn't it?
老大不想让她紧张 要善待美食 不是吗?

891
01:06:56,570 --> 01:06:57,970
Milady!
殿下!

892
01:06:58,370 --> 01:07:00,270
Psst! Milady!
噗嘶! 殿下!

893
01:07:00,970 --> 01:07:03,970
Oh, my little mouse! It's you.
哦 我的小老鼠! 是你

894
01:07:04,270 --> 01:07:06,570
I will deliver you from this evil, ma'am.
我会救你出来的 殿下

895
01:07:06,670 --> 01:07:08,670
Oh, no. Just go find my father.
哦不 你去找我的父亲

896
01:07:09,370 --> 01:07:11,170
Take this chain from around my neck.
拿着我脖子上这条项链

897
01:07:11,270 --> 01:07:13,070
To show him you are honest and truthful.
向他证明你的诚实 可靠

898
01:07:13,170 --> 01:07:16,570
Oh, I am! Honest and truthful and loyal and...
我本来就是啊! 诚实 可靠 忠诚...

899
01:07:16,670 --> 01:07:17,770
I know.
我知道

900
01:07:17,870 --> 01:07:18,870
But hurry.
不过要快

901
01:07:19,070 --> 01:07:20,470
Here. Take it.
来 拿着

902
01:07:20,770 --> 01:07:22,370
There isn't much time.
没有多少时间了

903
01:09:10,670 --> 01:09:12,270
Hey, did you get some? - Oh, yeah.
- 嘿 拿了吗? - 当然

904
01:09:12,370 --> 01:09:13,770
Here you are, sir.
这个给您 先生

905
01:09:13,770 --> 01:09:14,870
Fresh worms.
新鲜的蠕虫

906
01:09:17,470 --> 01:09:18,470
Thank you.
谢谢

907
01:09:23,570 --> 01:09:26,070
Well done, Roscuro!
干的漂亮 Roscuro!

908
01:09:26,670 --> 01:09:27,970
You hear that?
听到了吗?

909
01:09:28,070 --> 01:09:30,270
That's all because of you.
这都是你的功绩

910
01:09:30,770 --> 01:09:35,070
Come, my friend. Look at your handiwork.
来 我的朋友 看看你的杰作

911
01:09:59,170 --> 01:10:02,470
King! King! Sire, your daughter is in danger!
国王! 国王! 陛下 您的女儿现在很危险!

912
01:10:02,570 --> 01:10:04,070
Sire, up here!
国王 往上看!

913
01:10:04,870 --> 01:10:07,770
Your Highness! Please, sir!
殿下! 求你了 先生!

914
01:10:10,270 --> 01:10:11,570
Oh, come on.
哦 拜托

915
01:10:18,670 --> 01:10:19,670
Hey, Sire!
嘿 陛下!

916
01:10:20,770 --> 01:10:22,370
Your Highness!
殿下!

917
01:10:22,570 --> 01:10:24,570
Look, Your Highness! Look!
看看啊 殿下 看看我!

918
01:10:24,670 --> 01:10:25,970
Hello, Mr. King!
你好 国王殿下!

919
01:10:26,470 --> 01:10:27,570
Hey, hello!
嘿 你好!

920
01:10:30,370 --> 01:10:32,070
Down here! Hello! Down here!
看下面! 喂! 看下面!

921
01:10:32,170 --> 01:10:33,770
Listen, your daughter is in danger!
听着 你女儿现在很危险!

922
01:10:33,870 --> 01:10:35,170
She's in a dungeon!
她在地牢里!

923
01:10:35,270 --> 01:10:36,670
You're the only one who can help!
只有你能救她!

924
01:10:36,770 --> 01:10:38,470
She sent me to get you!
是她让我来找你的!

925
01:10:38,570 --> 01:10:39,770
Sir, please! Sir...
先生 求你了! 先生...

926
01:10:40,170 --> 01:10:41,370
Ooh! Sire!
陛下!

927
01:10:41,470 --> 01:10:42,870
Your Highness!
殿下!

928
01:10:42,870 --> 01:10:47,270
Look down here! Whoa!
往 下 看!

929
01:10:57,870 --> 01:10:59,870
Dad? Dad, listen. You've got to help me.
爸? 爸 听我说 你得帮帮我

930
01:10:59,970 --> 01:11:01,970
But you're dead!
